<!--\'b6 24. --> I do not, however, merely aim to "resurrect the old." When the old is raised up again, the old shell is cast off and a new life shines forth. The fetters of time no longer apply in this new life. It is eternally young, eternally new. My aim is in this way to extoll the eternally present life. I feel a presentiment of a great path that converges in the heart of all idols. And I feel that all human efforts, past and future, in extremis will be gathered in the direction of this path. The eternally present life on this path is dancing with joy. My prayer is that others may see the scene that I have endeavored to paint.}